Windows 11 Hyper-V allows native network address translation (NAT) for a virtual network.
The default switch changes IP/Subnet after each reboot.
Creation of a custom switch/NAT can be used in HyperV.
https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-server/virtualization/hyper-v/setup-nat-network

New-VMSwitch -SwitchName "HyperVNAT" -SwitchType Internal 
Get-NetAdapter
(note InterfaceIndex #)
New-NetIPAddress -IPAddress 172.26.27.1 -PrefixLength 24 -InterfaceIndex 53
New-NetNat -Name HyperVNAT -InternalIPInterfaceAddressPrefix 172.26.27.0/24 
